ics, and a noteworthy monody on the death of his son. Extensive introductory notes and annotations place these translations in their literary and historical contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aRhetoric, Ancient. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  a4th century ad.  aancient civilizations.  aancient greece.  aannotations.  acustomary declarations.  adeath of son.  aeducated community.  aemperor julian.  aenglish translation.  aextensive introductory notes.  afamous speeches.  ahimerius of athens.  ahistorical context.  alife in athens.  aliterary context.  amonody.  arhetcomp.  arhetoric and composition.  asurviving orations.  ateacher of rhetoric.1 aPenella, Robert J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025093240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093371240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520933712423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520933712/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY